How can VUE help

1. create dynamic applications
2. tools for code organization
3. Speed of development
4. Developer tools
5. Helps with scaling

Features and benefits:

1. Virtual DOM
2. Lightweight (10k gzip)
3. Progressive
4. VUE ecosystem
5. flexible
6. Incrementally adoptable

You have mustache syntax here

in vue you have directives like v-model, just like HTML attributes
<input v-model="greeting" />
v-if is like an if statement in js

//here if you put is visible false then the box dissapears

 <div v-if="isVisible" class="box"></div>
 let app = Vue.createApp({
        data: function () {
          return {
            greeting: "Hello Vue3!",
            isVisible: false,
          };
        },
      });
      v-show is like v-if
 <div v-show="isVisible" class="box"></div>

v-if for loading spinner
v-show specific cases, toggle something more sepcifically

 <div v-else-if="isVisible2" class="box"></div>
      <div v-else="isVisible" class="box"></div>

This is cool

<style> as well
<button v-on:click="isVisible=!isVisible">Toggle Box</button>
      <div v-if="isVisible" class="box"></div>

@click replaces the v-on:click
 <button @click="isVisible=!isVisible">Toggle Box</button>

      <input @keyup.enter="greet" v-model="greeting" />
